        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", because then he was guilty of a new crime, to wit, a contempt of God’s ordinance, and a gross neglect of the duty of self-preservation, and therefore deserved death from God, who might permit it to be inflicted by the avenger of blood. ",
        "children": []
